    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="311" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                <head>No. 311.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pak Chung
                                    Yang</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Corea</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-07-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 16, 1888</date>.
                                (Received July 17.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I am
                            in receipt of advices from my country today to the effect that the
                            Corean telegraph line has been completed to Fusan, connecting with the
                            Japanese cable at that point. Hereafter we shall send our telegraphic
                            dispatches to Seoul by this route.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to remain, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pak Chung
                                    Yang.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
